# Cursor Rules for SlotSmart
# These rules guide AI behavior in Cursor IDE

## Project Context

Project: SlotSmart
Type: SaaS Web Application - Tennis Club Management
Tech Stack: ASP.NET Core (.NET 10), React, TypeScript, Material UI, Entity Framework Core, PostgreSQL

## AI Framework Integration

This project uses the Supervisor-Worker AI Framework.
- Framework location: docs/SUPERVISOR/
- Always check CURRENT-STATUS.md before major work
- Follow role protocols (SUPERVISOR or WORKER)
- Methodology skills available in .cursor/skills/

## Coding Standards

### Language: C# (Backend)

- Use async/await throughout - never sync-over-async (.Result, .Wait())
- Follow Clean Architecture: Domain → Application → Infrastructure → Presentation
- Domain entities must NOT reference Infrastructure concerns
- Use DTOs for all API contracts (never expose domain entities directly)
- Use UUIDv7 for all entity identifiers
- Use Result pattern or exceptions consistently (choose one per project)
- All inputs must be validated (FluentValidation or DataAnnotations)
- Prefer records for immutable DTOs and value objects
- Use dependency injection for all dependencies

### Language: TypeScript (Frontend)

- Strict TypeScript enabled - no `any` types
- Functional React components with hooks only
- Separate API calls into dedicated service files
- Use MUI components for consistency
- Handle loading and error states in all async operations

### General Rules

- Follow existing patterns in the codebase
- Keep controllers thin (delegate to application layer)
- Keep functions/methods small and focused
- Add XML doc comments for public APIs (C#)
- Handle errors appropriately at each layer
- Write testable code (use DI, avoid static/singleton state)

### File Naming

- C# files: PascalCase matching class name (`TrainingService.cs`)
- TypeScript files: camelCase for files, PascalCase for components (`TrainingCard.tsx`)
- Test files: match source + `.Tests.cs` or `.test.ts`

### C# Namespace Conventions

- `SlotSmart.Domain.[Entity]`
- `SlotSmart.Application.[Feature].[UseCase]`
- `SlotSmart.Infrastructure.[Provider]`
- `SlotSmart.Api.[Controller]`

### Import Organization (TypeScript)

1. React imports
2. External library imports (MUI, etc.)
3. Internal imports (services, components, types)

## Testing Requirements

- Write unit tests for all business logic (Application and Domain layers)
- Use TDD: write failing test first, then implementation
- Run tests before committing: `dotnet test`
- Minimum 80% coverage for business logic
- Test command: `dotnet test`

## Multi-Tenant Rules

- ALWAYS filter data by ClubId in queries
- NEVER return data from a different club
- Multi-tenant isolation must be verified in tests
- ClubId must flow from auth token, not user input

## Documentation

- Update CHANGELOG.md after changes (newest first, follow keepachangelog.com format)
- Update README if adding major features
- Document complex domain logic with XML comments
- Keep docs/SUPERVISOR/ status current

## What to Avoid

- Don't put business logic in controllers
- Don't reference Infrastructure from Domain layer
- Don't use sync blocking calls in async context
- Don't hardcode connection strings or secrets
- Don't skip multi-tenant filtering
- Don't expose domain entities in API responses (use DTOs)
- Don't change multi-tenant isolation without architectural review

## Preferred Patterns

### Repository Pattern
Use repository interfaces in Domain layer, implement in Infrastructure. Never query DbContext directly from Application layer.

### CQRS (if adopted)
Separate Commands (write) from Queries (read). Commands return Result, Queries return DTOs.

### Error Handling
Use ProblemDetails for API error responses. Log errors at appropriate levels (Error for failures, Warning for expected issues).

## Common Tasks

### Adding a new API endpoint
1. Define DTO in Application layer
2. Write failing test for use case
3. Implement use case (Application layer)
4. Add controller action (Presentation layer)
5. Add integration test
6. Update CHANGELOG

### Adding a new domain entity
1. Define entity in Domain layer (no EF annotations in Domain)
2. Define repository interface in Domain
3. Write EF configuration in Infrastructure
4. Implement repository in Infrastructure
5. Write unit tests
6. Update CHANGELOG

### Fixing a bug
1. Write a failing test reproducing the bug
2. Fix the bug
3. Verify test passes
4. Check for similar patterns
5. Update CHANGELOG

## Session Protocol

Start of session:
- Read docs/SUPERVISOR/CURRENT-STATUS.md
- Check DELEGATION-TRACKER for active work
- Understand current priorities

End of session:
- Update CURRENT-STATUS if changed
- Update CHANGELOG if code changed
- Create handover notes if incomplete

---

# SlotSmart-Specific Rules

## Domain Model Rules
- Club is the aggregate root for multi-tenancy
- Member has exactly one Role at a time
- Booking belongs to both Member and Training
- MemberRelation links Parent members to Player members
- Training can be recurring (has schedule) or one-time
- Booking capacity must respect Training.MaxCapacity

## API Conventions
- Use plural nouns for collections: `/api/clubs`, `/api/members`
- Use nested routes for owned resources: `/api/clubs/{clubId}/members`
- Return 201 Created for POST with Location header
- Return 204 No Content for DELETE
- Use pagination for collections (PageNumber, PageSize)
